        <odd id="ref7">
            <head>Early American History Note</head>
            <p>This collection contains a series of letters written by Edward Piggot to various correspondents while held as prisoner of war at Fontainebleau by Napoleon. The letters are written in French and English and recount his time in jail. He also discusses his work in natural history, and among the topics he discusses is a paper he wrote for the Royal Society on astronomy.</p>
        </odd>
        <bioghist id="ref3">
            <head>Biographical/Historical note</head>
            <p>Edward Piggott was a British amateur scientist and astronomer.</p>
        </bioghist>
